          "date": "2024-09-06 13:54:58.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-18070 tests: fix sanity test_103a",
        "message": "LU-18070 tests: fix sanity test_103a\n\nOn recent distributions like Ubuntu 24.04, the default behavior for\ndefault ACLs is different than on other distros.\nSo to make sure we do not inherit unwanted default ACLs, make sure\nthey are cleaned up before adding any other ACLs.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity env=ONLY=103a mdscount=2 mdtcount=4 osscount=1 ostcount=8 clientcount=2 clientdistro=el9.4\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity env=ONLY=103a mdscount=2 mdtcount=4 osscount=1 ostcount=8 clientcount=2 clientdistro=ubuntu2404\nSigned-off-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I72a2a193357fc04186980bb3dec87ff2d62e2f21\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
